</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="ccffd147-9a12-467b-ad33-7f98c339dbd5">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 6</note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>This add-on allows you to find a day of the week corresponding to a chosen date.</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="32bf4e4f-08ed-4f43-b50f-1d2527951e06">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 8</note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>It adds a submenu in the NVDA Tools menu named "Day of the week", containing 2 items:</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="2dc425a6-be4b-4930-82e9-05dca78965c1">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 10</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix: * </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>The first one named "Search a day", opens a dialog composed of 3 controls:</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="7ae4b5e0-51ee-4cb1-9b39-c456ba0b9d5a">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 12</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix:     * </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>A listbox to choose or type your date;</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="bc4fad54-f2e6-42ec-a502-3ed69ee61245">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 13</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix:     * </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>An "OK" button to display a messageBox containing your day;</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="16fbddfd-79f9-4f1a-831a-3f86f86c3829">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 14</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix:     * </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>A "Cancel" button to close the dialog.</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="678ad63a-1a47-4150-aead-2aa100e53881">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 16</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix: * </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>The second one named "dayOfTheWeek add-on settings" opens the parameters of the add-on to specify whether you want to report labels for date fields or not, it is composed of the following elements:</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="c14dddd1-b927-46b0-a1a0-b9cd47264559">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 18</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix:     * </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>Enable accessibility of the date selector;</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="dcd16c89-1d99-4f74-8445-b79a471fab30">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 19</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix:     * </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>Level of the announces of labels, you will then have 3 choices:</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="fe4edf45-173b-4627-9ca5-9d0094924953">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 21</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix:         * </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>Long (it's the default choice);</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="1ec20dd3-b9f4-434f-b756-323dbebdd22a">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 22</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix:         * </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>Short (for short announcements);</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="840f5192-5242-40f8-8ad7-31a8c46bee87">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 23</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix:         * </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>Off (to disable labels announcements).</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="b16399c5-0324-4a0e-98dd-83eca64375ab">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 25</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix:     * </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>Enable announcement of the current date field value only, when moving vertically;</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="020fe712-5144-44c8-9c29-ca842e324c36">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 26</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix:     * </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>An "OK" button to save your configuration;</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="4e71dcd5-855f-41d2-b67b-62330ab40551">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 27</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix:     * </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>A "Cancel" button to cancel and close the dialog.</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="213ca5f3-c3c6-4459-ad56-9de24af3a4c3">
<notes>
